# 06_resolver_closest — proof closest_name considers all naming surfaces.
#
# Asks for `tb_no` — a one-character typo of `tb_nod` (a real registry
# entry post-s188 m1). Edit distance is 1. Should produce a "did you
# mean 'tb_nod'?" suggestion.
#
# This validates that closest_name_across_columns walks the live
# registry as one of its candidate pools. Without that, only DB names
# would be suggested; with it, real registry entries also surface.
#
# Pre-s188 this script asked for `tool.nod` and the suggestion was
# `tool.node` — the hand-picked s186 m2 name. The funnel migration
# replaced `tool.node` with `tb_nod` (every tool button addressable
# by its widget_names.db abbrev), so the typo target moved with it.
#
# Expected output:
#
#   > tb_no click
#   error unknown object 'tb_no' (did you mean 'tb_nod'?)
#
# The suggestion can also surface near-matches from widget_names.db's
# long_name column — e.g. a typo of `main_toolbar_node_tool_btn` would
# suggest the full name, then the resolver would translate to `tb_nod`
# on retry. The closest-name pool is union: live registry abbrevs +
# DB abbrevs + DB long_names.

tb_no click
